MBOMBELA – Lowvelder understands that residents on the Delta line will be affected from 15:00. The power utility has not implemented load shedding since December 9. In a statement on Sunday, Eskom cited a shortage of capacity for the decision. “There is also a need to replenish and preserve emergency water and diesel resources to limit load shedding possibility or magnitude thereof in the following week.”  ALSO READ:Cyril Ramaphosa’s Eskom plans ‘a war against the poor’ Eskom continues to urge the public to use resources sparingly.